bioghist.p:
Many of A. Conger Goodyear's writings were privately printed for
			 distribution to friends and family members. Most of them can be found either in
			 this collection or in the BECHS library; they include the following titles: 
		  The Museum of Modern Art, the First Ten Years
			 (1943); 
		  John George Milburn Jr.: A Memoir (1938); 
		  [Goodyear] Family History, By a Descendant
		  (194-?); 
		  One Wide Expanse (1946); 
		  The Loq of the Yakima (1903?); and 
		   Sidelights (1960). The Spring 1961 issue of

		  Niagara Frontier also features a sketch
		  of his mother.
